<br>
Kali, a human of about 14 years, sat at the table with her chin on the palms of her hands, elbows resting on the hard plank of a dining surface, staring dreamily at the red-headed elf. Hamin was busy looking about for the waitress, his stein nearing an appalling state of emptyness. <br>
<br>
&quot;This city chomps. I have to find a better place to hang out. Humans are too... hairy.&quot; The bard sneered while staring at his lute, then looked up at a slightly crest-fallen Kali, before adding under his breath &quot;Present company excepted, of course&quot;. Kuladen forced a smile and the human relaxed, and returned to her staring. <br>
<br>
Hamin stood abruptly, growling something about the service in this 'hole' and stomped off. Kuladen shook his head and lowered his feet from the table, setting his lute aside. Since he was saddled with this girl for the day, he figured he should make the best of it. He would have to have words with Hamin about his idea for 'win-a-day-with-the-bard' contest, and how out of the hundreds of attractive of-age women who entered, the dwarf picked this waif of a sewer-rat girl who obviously has never seen a brush in her life. Standing slightly shorter than the elf, Kali sported a mop of raven hair, mangled into a hairstyle that the humans found attractive that week. Wearing nothing but a two sizes too big tunic and slippers, the potato sack grey dress was tied off at the waist with a brown leather belt, apparently this girl's prize posession. <br>
<br>
Kuladen looked around again, then his eyes settled on the girl. Head raised in anticipation, the girl leaned forward to listen to anything the elf might say. <br>
<br>
&quot;So.. uhm.. do you like to do.. stuff?&quot;<br>
<br>
The girl's eyes grew even larger than before, and instantly her mouth opened up and words came forth like the rains of karana. Wincing, the elf unconciously leaned back to protect himself from the onslaught of words from this girl, describing her days then her life then her best friend 'Jemolaa' who was 'NEVERgoingtobelievethis!'. After a moment of listening Kuladen spied Hamin walking towards the table, only to make a small circle and walk away from the table after spotting the look of contempt in the elf's eyes. <br>
<br>
'SoandthisonetimeIwasatyourconcerthereinFreeportandmyfriendYahnnsaidthatthemilitiahadsomething againstyouandthisonetime themilitacaughtmyfriendthagglookingat....'<br>
<br>
Kuladen leaned back and tuned the girl out again. Several minutes passed as the bard watched people enter and leave the tavern, a couple people going so far as to approach his table for an interview or an autograph before leaving, unable to get a word in edgewise. Sighing, Kuladen removed his feet from the table again. Softly he said &quot;If you shut up I'll sing a song&quot;<br>
<br>
'aremeanttokillyoubutIhavenevermetanyonewhodiedbyeatingfirebeetleeyesbutthisonetimemyfriend Jemolaa,thesameonewholikesBobbyFisher,remember?,tookabiteofoneandyouknowwhatstartedto glow?THAT'SRight!Her....'<br>
<br>
The girl paused, and looked at the elf dumbfounded, and nodded eagerly. Mentally stopclocking the time it took for her brain to register what he said, the elf forced another sweet smile and stood, picking up his lute. The bar hushed as he walked towards the stage, not even pausing to grab a certain Coldain Dwarf's ear as he walked by a group trying to hide Hamin from the elf. 'Ow'ing the dwarf followed, and climbed up onto the stage next to the elf. <br>
<br>
Leaning into the gnomish voice amplifier and attention getter Kuladen cleared his throat. &quot;This is a song I just thought of. I would like to dedicate it to the winner of 'Spend a day with the bard' contest put on by this Tavern and The Emerald Shop. The Emerald Shop.. if you have the honey we have the money.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kuladen stepped back and tuned his lute for a minute. Hamin beside him crossed his arm and grumped, not even knowing why he had to stand on stage for a song he didn't even know. <br>
<br>
&quot;This song is called 'Shut the Hell up' &quot;<br>
<br>
Two musical notes escaped the lute before a resounding chord of dissonance ripped through the tavern, the bard dropping his lute and leaping backwards. A crossbow bolt protruded from the wood, and the strings had snapped and raked the elf across the face. Standing hunched over, hands covering a bloodied face, the elf heard the distinct sound of around a dozen Crossbows being cocked. A small scream erupted from a nearby table, and Kuladen didn't have to look up to know that Kali was the one responsible for the totally off-key wail. <br>
<br>
&quot;You are under arrest for the attempted murder of Sir Lucan, brave protector and stalwart member of the Freeport Militia.&quot;<br>
<br>
Groaning, the elf stood up straight, suddenly remembering why he hated the city so much. Ignoring the blood running down his face, he raised two hands in front of him. <br>
<br>
&quot;Can't we talk about this fellas?&quot;<br>
<br>
