<br>
&quot;Yous attack Sir Lucan. Yous die in here.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kuladen puffed out his chest, and crossed his arms. &quot;I await my trail. A jury of my peers will vindicate me.&quot; <br>
<br>
The jailer paused for a second, and the keys stopped spinning in his shock. He then bust out laughing, and as he closed the jail block door behind him the sounds of him laughing resounded across the stone room.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yer an idiot&quot; <br>
<br>
Kuladen looked over to see Hamin had pulled himself onto the lower of the two bunks, and say with his arms crossed, staring at the red-headed elf. &quot;You ain't gettin' no fair trial&quot;<br>
<br>
Peering at his surroundings, Kuladen answered off-handedly &quot;You're the one who is an idiot for booking a gig in Freeport when you knew I was wanted&quot;. Picking up a rock, Kuladen squeezed it and realized that it was in fact a sponge, and probably was the only way he would attempt to stay clean. The room was sparse, three stone walls and a wall of bars, with a single barred window in the back of the cell to allow some light in. The place was dark, though, and damp. The place smelled too much like mildew, and the floor was covered with a thin layer of slime. Being the spring time, a wind was coming into the window bringing what would be a fresh supply of air, if the city planners had not placed the jail house next to the city's stables. <br>
<br>
Flies roamed everywhere, and with a sneer the elf swatted them away from himself. <br>
<br>
Leaning against the bars, the bard winced as he slid a bit, the same slime that coated the walls and floor had also attached itself to the metal. &quot;Well. I guess it couldn't get any worse.&quot;<br>
<br>
Hamin's eyes grew wide and he mouthed 'no' when the sudden sound of thunder struck in the distance, and as the sound died down they heard a high pitched drone coming towards the cell block. The door opened up and the jailer re-emerged, ducking to get into such a small area. Walking towards their cell the duo could see that he carried Kali, who was talking non-stop as she was being tossed into the cell next to the two. <br>
<br>
