<br>
The dwarf stood, walked over to the elf, who was busy staring in shock as the jailer exited the cell block, in a fowler temper than before. The bard felt a tugging sensation and turned to find Hamin progressively pulling himself closer and closer to the dwarf's face. Stopping mere inches away, the dwarf sneered through his beard. &quot;I told you never to say things couldn't get worse&quot;<br>
